6. var vs let
var	let
Function Scope	Block Scope
Redeclare Allowed	Not Allowed
Hoisted	Hoisted but TDZ
Old JS	ES6

Example

if(true){

var a=10;

}

console.log(a);

Output

10

Now

if(true){

let a=10;

}

console.log(a);

Output

Reference Error

Why?

Because let is Block Scoped.

Interview Answer

var is function scoped while let is block scoped. let also prevents accidental redeclaration.

