17. Currying

Don't worry.

This sounds difficult but is very easy.

Suppose we have

add(2,3)

Currying converts it into

add(2)(3)

Instead of giving all arguments together,

We give them one by one.

Example

function add(a){
    return function(b){
        return a+b;
    }
}

add(5)(3);

Output

8
Real-life Example

Buying pizza

Normal

Choose Size
Choose Topping
Pay

Currying

Choose Size

↓

Now choose Topping

↓

Now Pay

One step at a time.

Interview Answer

Currying converts a function with multiple arguments into multiple functions that each take one argument.

